title: BJP is giving tough contest to Congress in Manipur
text:
BJP is giving tough contest to Congress in Manipur BJP is giving tough contest to Congress in Manipur The early trends suggest the Congress leading on 10 seats, the BJP on 10 as well. By: ANI | Imphal | Published: March 11, 2017 3:30 PM The counting of votes for 60-member assembly is currently underway at eleven centres in Manipur. (PTI) 
The Bharatiya Janata Party ( BJP ) is giving a tough fight to the Congress in Manipur. The early trends suggest the Congress leading on 10 seats, the BJP on 10 as well. The NPF is leading on three and others on seven seats respectively. 
Manipur Chief Minister Okram Ibobi Singh has won from Thoubal seat. The counting of votes for 60-member assembly is currently underway at eleven centres in Manipur. Meanwhile, in a major setback for the Congress in Uttarakhand, the BJP as per the latest trends is emerging as the frontrunner to form the next government in the hill state. 
Also watch: 
With 50 seats, the BJP has established a significant lead. As per latest trends, the Indian National Congress (INC) has bagged 10 seats while other parties have bagged four seats in the 70-member Uttarakhand Assembly. 
Contrary to the 2012 assembly polls, the BJP has been successful in defeating the Congress with a substantial lead in this yearâ€™s polls.
